{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_oliver_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280600611/1930091401/0605.xml":{"full_text":"A-6\nWINS $lO,OOO SUIT\nf FOR FALSE ARREST\nWoman Was Put in Ward Be\ncause She Would Not Ac\ncept Imposter as Son.\nSy the Associated Press.\nLOS ANGELES, September 13.\u2014Mrs.\nChristine Collins was awarded $lO,BOO\ndfcj&ages by a Superior Court Jury last\nnight against Police Capt. J. J. Jones,\nwho placed her in the psychopathic\nward two years ago, after she refused\nto accept an imposter as her son. She\naued for $55,300.\nHoax Is Perpetrated.\n'the trial revealed the story of how J\na 10-year-old boy, Arthur Hutchins, jr..\nof De Kalb, 111., perpetrated a hoax on j\noAcers of two States and passed for a 1\nmonth as Walter Collins, 9, who was i\n\u2022lain on Gordon Stewart Northcott's\nWlnevijle, Calif., chicken ranch.\nYoung Hutchins, a runaway, read\nnewspaper stories of the search for the\nCollins boy,\" who had been missing sev\neral months, and tolcl police in Texas\nhe was the missing lad. Capt. Jones re\nturned him to LoS Angeles, and Arthur\nidentified Walter's playthings without\nhesitation. Mrs. Collins, complaining\nArthur \u201cis too thin and tall,\" was per\nsuaded to take him home.\nA week later she returned him to\nthe police, saying he was not her son.\nAt the trigl she testified Capt. bines\nthen said: \u201cYou are crazy, and not fit\nto be at large.\u201d She was placed in\nthe. psychopathic ward and remained\nthere, five days A few days later\nyoung Hutchins confessed the hoax, de\nclaring \u201cit was easy to fool the police.\u201d\nHe .w 'tig returned to relatives in De\nKalb.\nBoy Was Murdered.\nSubsequently it was discovered Wal\nter Had been murdered. Mrs. Sarah\nLouise Northcott, mother of Gordon\nStewart Northcott, pleaded guilty to\nthe murder and is serving a life sen\ntence In San Quefitin Penitentiary. Her\nson confessed his part in the slaying,\nwas convicted of the murder of three\nothet hoys and is aw-aiting execution\nOctober 2 at San Quentin.\nJudge Edwin F. Hahn, who presided\nat* the trial of Mrs. Collin's suit, in*\nstrutted the Jury Capt. Jones did not\nhave probable cause for committing the\nwoman to the psychopathic Ward. It\nremained only for the Jury to fix the\namount of damages.\nRESORT r OFFERS OUTING\nON INSTALLMENT PLAN\nCoupon Tickets Good f<* Two\nWeeks to, Bs Issued to\nV Boost Trad#.\nBCHWETZINOEN, Germany VP)\nVacations on the Installment plan are\nthis German Summer resort's answer to\nthe'world-wide business depression which\nIs keeping too mafiy people at home.\nPicturesquely situated between Hei\ndelberg and the Rhino and famous alike\nibr Its palace gardens, rivaling Ver\nsailles, and the unrivaled succulence of\nthe asparagus it feeds its. Summer\nboarders, Schwetzingen has decided to\nissue coupon. tickets good for a two-.\nweak visit, half to be paid down and\nth* balance id monthly installments Os\n$2.40.\nThe coupons are good not only for\nboard and room but also for side trips\nto Heidelberg and other points of in\ntersst.\nWE DELIVER\nLEROY\u2019S\n709 D St. N.W.\ny OssmM* Kinn'i National 1 *54\nK AU Luggage and\n4 Sporting Goods at 1\n4 y 3 to y 2 Off to Make\nSpace for Toys i\ni L\u00abatl'* r Bags\ni llw ll with Straps y\n55.90\ny I\u2014slo Leathar ear 4\nBallows Case.... OD.UU 4 f\n4 1\u2014512.95 Leather Gladstone\nk Case with straps. QA n y\nSim 24 oU.sJU y\ny 3\u201457.95 Fibre Cases, cloth 4\n4 lined and straps. \u00bbS Qh\ni Sim 28 1\n&\u2014ss Over- y\nnight Cases 4\n4 JUT Silk Lined 4\n4 L J Sizes 16 to 20 j\n52.97\n10\u201453.50 Overnight Cases, B\nsquare corners, A1 Afl\n1 4 aims 16 to 18.... vi\u00bbv' C\n4 s\u2014s 2 Overnight QQ r 4\nCases \u2022JiH' 1\n1 6\u2014ss Leather e>A Qnf 1 y\n4 y Bags I*. I 4 y\ny 2\u20145-> Full Size Wardrobe y\n4 Trunks, open 518.75 V\n1\u2014529.50 Stearryr Wardrobe 4\n4 Trunk, best con- QAI hr\n4 struction Ofal*l D y\n:4 MISCELLANEOUS\n4 CLOSE-OUTS y\n12\u201465 c Crab OC<\u00bb\ny Nets 4\n4 35\u20142